raw_data.title: IT Project Scheduler
raw_data.description: Directly supports projects by proactively implementing processes and methodologies related to planning, scheduling, cost analysis, estimating, risk assessment and resource requirements. Performs all aspects of schedule control functions including review and analysis of time impact analysis, critical path assessments and creation/maintenance of project schedules. Employs analytical skills and the use of software to summarize project data into tailored information to facilitate communication across various levels of the organization. Builds various reports including resource histograms, commodity curves, milestone reports, etc.  Proven experience performing project controls, including planning, estimating, forecasting, scheduling, and project reports. Knowledge of methods used to develop and maintain critical path schedules, reporting status and schedule scenarios to present to the project team. Ability to clearly communicate with   developers,   project   managers,   and   asset   managers, leveraging   software   development    life cycle. Demonstrated ability to communicate verbally and in writing. Demonstrated ability to work independently. Ability to develop full life cycle IT software development schedules following specific a methodology (rolling wave, water fall or agile).  Bachelor’s Degree Experience: Five (5) years relevant experience.

raw_data.title: Technical Project Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for directing the operations of assigned project(s) to include planning, initiating, managing, executing and closing out of mission-oriented programs, projects, and/or tasks. This includes responsibility for risk mitigation, work control, planning, scheduling, infrastructure, and performance monitoring. May perform any or all of the following: technical support, supervision of staff, development of work breakdown structures and budgets. Develops well-defined procedures/processes in the delivery of practical mission-oriented solutions using best commercial management practices that may include Project Management Institute (PMI) processes and procedures. Prepares reports, white papers, and summaries of analyses, presentations, tables, and evaluations.  Project Managers have progressive experience in managing, directing, and implementing information technology projects. Project Managers will have the skills requisite to perform the functions described in the client’s statement of work. Experience in managerial and technical leadership directing and supporting a broad range of Information Technology (IT) efforts requiring both specialized and diverse knowledge. Advanced knowledge of scientific or engineering principals, theories and concepts to accomplish the objective of a total program, project or system. Develops or directs development of solutions to problems. Demonstrated ability to formulate work standards, develop schedules and control costs. Knowledge of the principles and concepts of management and business best practices and procedures. Demonstrated capacity to plan, organize, allocate, and coordinate resources. Experience providing team leadership and delegating and developing subordinates. Familiarity with accounting methods and MS Project to manage and ensure project remains within cost. Demonstrated business sense. Excellent oral/written communications skills.   Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Management, Operations Research, Statistics, Mathematics, Engineering, or related field.
